column24: PSD unit has been recruiting COVID-19 patients starting from March 2019 during the first pandemic outbreak. Patients were admitted to the COVID-19 ward or to intensive care units and blood was harvested within 7 days after admission. Samples were processed, divided in aliquots and stored at -80 °C in the PSD biobank according to BMRI guidelines. The Biobank also keep record of the signed patient consensus forms. Platelet poor plasma (PPP) samples were then transferred to Firalis. Sample/data couples were anonymized before shipping. The cohort main characteristics are: 63% males, age 67.74±11.49 (median years±SD), 40% intubated, 25% required O2 therapy, 24% CPAP in ward; 11% displayed mild disease, 25% died and 75% were eventually discharged. The main comorbidities were: T2DM 20%, obesity 19% and hypertension 54% of the cases .
column25: The PROVID-PROGRESS Study is a prospective, longitudinal, observational, multi-center study of hospitalized Patients positive for SARS-CoV-2 with the aim to identify clinical and molecular markers of disease progression and new therapies.
column26: The PROVID-CAPNETZ Study is a prospective, longitudinal, observational, multi-center study of hospitalized Patients positive for SARS-CoV-2 with the aim to identify clinical and molecular markers of disease progression and new therapies.
column27: This consisted on hospitalized adults (men and women =>18 years of age at the time of inclusion in the study), who can provide written informed consent before beginning any study procedure. Confirmation of SARS-CoV-2 infection by a microbiological test performed before randomization, no longer than 72 hours. Patients were no included when presenting: comorbidities that imply a poor prognosis; pregnancy or breast-feeding; serious or active bacterial infections by pathogens other than SARS-CoV-2; immunosuppressive treatment; previous evidence of latent untreated tuberculosis.
